Bus drivers affiliated to Great North Transport (GNT) reportedly brought traffic in the central business district of Polokwane to a standstill early yesterday (Wednesday) morning when parking and abandoning close to ten buses at busy intersections along the main street. Grobler and Jorissen Streets were blocked at the intersections with Landdros Maré Street, causing traffic to build up for a distance. At the time of going to press the Provincial Police’s liaison unit said no arrests had been made or cases opened at that stage.
